    public class Plank
extends javax.swing.JButton
    Models a plank. This class represents a JButton object of a plank. When combined with the Create map class, instances of the Plank class can be displayed on the window.

      • Plank

        public Plank​(int x,
             int y,
             int length,
             boolean visible,
             boolean isHorizontal)
        Constructor. Create an instance of plank with the given parameters
        参数:
        x - the x position of the plank in the map
        y - the y position of the plank in the map
        length - the length of the whole plank
        visible - distinguish whether the plank is visible, which means there is a plank or not
        isHorizontal - distinguish the condition of the plank

      • Plank

        public Plank​(int x,
             int y,
             int horizontalLength,
             int verticalLength,
             boolean isHorizontal,
             boolean visible,
             boolean isComplex)
        参数:
        x - the x position of the plank in the map
        y - the y position of the plank in the map
        horizontalLength - the length of the whole plank for the horizontal one
        verticalLength - the length of the whole plank for the vertical one
        isHorizontal - distinguish the condition of the plank
        visible - distinguish whether the plank is visible, which means there is a plank or not
        isComplex - distinguish whether the plank can be used in two planks

        public void setWarningString​(int i)
        Set a new window
        参数:
        i - the condition of warning string; 1: player is not near the plank 2: the length of currentPlank does not fit this plank 3: User wants to put the plank but there has been a plank 4: User wants to pick this plank but he/she has carried a plank 5: User wants to pick this plank but there is no plank 6: User wants to put a plank but he/she does not carry a plank
